<title type="html"><![CDATA[1/9 (Thu.) Make Your New Year’s Resolutions count/How to ensure your privacy &amp; safety around smart devices (Host: Nikki)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=352&amp;p=368#p368"><![CDATA[
First session:  One Thing You Can Do: Make Your New Year’s Resolutions count <br />                     (From The New York Times)<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/01/climate/nyt-climate-newsletter-resolutions-fireworks.html">https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/01/clim ... works.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br /><br />1. Why should we care about what happens to the polar ice caps?<br />2. What climate change impacts have you noticed?<br />3. How does climate change affect local plants and trees?<br />4. Will the remedies to climate change be worse than the disease? Will it drive more people into poverty with higher costs?<br />5. What can you do as individual to slow down climate change?<br /><br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Second session: How to ensure your privacy and safety around smart devices<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/editorials/archives/2020/01/04/2003728682">http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/editori ... 2003728682</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br /><br />1. What smart devices have you used? How is your experience?<br />2. Have you used any way to protect your privacy? Are they effective?<br />3. What’s your opinion on a “smart home”?<br />4. How will a smart home look like in the future?<br /><br /><br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 pm - 7:20 pm Free talk<br />7:20 pm - 8:00 pm First topic discussion<br />8:00 pm - 8:30 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited)<br />8:30 pm - 9:00 pm Second topic discussion<br />speaker time: 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time: 3 minutes<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第三區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=25437">Michael</a> — Sun Jan 05, 2020 10:36 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
